Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setObjFPlanBox(25.10)                                    setObjFPlanBox(25.10)

Name
       setObjFPlanBox  -  Defines the bounding box of a specified object, even
       outside the core boundary

Syntax
        setObjFPlanBox

       [-help]

       objectType

       objectName

       llx lly urx ury

       [-no_snap_to_grid]

       Defines the bounding box of a specified object, even outside  the  core
       boundary. You can use this command after importing the design.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each setObjFPlanBox parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man setObjFPlanBox

       <objectName>
              Specifies the name of the object for <objectType>.

              Data_type: string, required

       <objectType>
              Specifies the type of object for objectName. This can be any  of
              the following:

              * Bump

              * Cell

              * Group

              * Instance

              * I/O cell

              * I/O pin

              * Layershape

              * Module

              * Net

              * Partition cut

              * Partition feedthrough

              * Partition pin block

              * Pin

              * Pin guide

              * Row cluster

              * Standard row

              Data_type: string, required

       <llx>  Specifies the lower left x coordinate of the object.

              Data_type: float, required

       <lly>  Specifies the lower left y coordinate of the object.

              Data_type: float, required

       <urx>  Specifies the upper right x coordinate of the object.

              Data_type: float, required

       <ury>  Specifies the upper right y coordinate of the object.

              Data_type: float, required

       -no_snap_to_grid
              When specified, the snap rules are not honored and a user speci-
              fied box is not snapped to the grid even if it overlaps with the
              die box.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
       The   following   command   specifies   a   bounding   box  for  module
       DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST at a lower left  x  coordinate  of  700.00,  a
       lower  left  y  coordinate  of  700.00, and upper right x coordinate of
       1000.00, and an upper right y coordinate of 1000.00:

       setObjFPlanBox Module DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST  700.00  700.00  1000.00
       1000.00

